=Definition=

From the Wikipedia:

"Neo-Luddism is a personal philosophy against modern technology. Its name is based on the historical legacy of the British Luddites which were active between 1811 and 1816.[1] Neo-luddism does not equate necessarily to outright technophobia and includes the critical examination of the effects technology has on individuals and communities."
(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neo-Luddism)

